## [2.0.0] - 2025-05-20

### Breaking Changes
- Removed support for Node.js versions below 16.0.0
- Changed default export structure (see migration guide)
- Renamed `initialize()` to `init()` for consistency
- Modified return type of `processData()` from object to Promise

### Added
- Full TypeScript rewrite with comprehensive type definitions
- New plugin system for extensibility
- Built-in caching mechanism for improved performance
- Comprehensive test suite with 95% coverage

### Changed
- Migrated from CommonJS to ES modules
- Updated all dependencies to latest stable versions
- Improved documentation with interactive examples
- Enhanced CLI with better help text and error handling

### Migration Guide
To upgrade from v1.x to v2.0.0:

1. Update Node.js to version 16 or higher
2. Change import statements:
   ```js
   // Old
   const package = require('your-package');
   
   // New
   import { init, processData } from 'your-package';
   ```
3. Update method calls:
   ```js
   // Old
   package.initialize(options);
   
   // New
   init(options);
   ```

